== Configuration ==

=== Service ===

==== OpenRC ====

To have automatically start BIND at system boot: 

{{RootCmd|rc-update add named default}}

To start the service now:

{{RootCmd|rc-service named start}}

Most management of BIND is done through its {{c|rndc}} command, although the {{Path|/etc/init.d/named}} (OpenRC) init script can be passed the following arguments, in addition the typical start/stop/restart routines:

; <code>checkconfig</code> : Validates the configuration file {{Path|/etc/bind/named.conf}} for correct syntax.
; <code>checkzones</code> : Validates the zone files for correct syntax.
; <code>reload</code> : Reloads the zone files without restarting the named daemon itself.

For example:

{{RootCmd|rc-service named reload}}

=== Chroots ===

System that will be using BIND in a chrooted environment should set the <var>CHROOT</var> variable in {{Path|/etc/conf.d/named}} accordingly. Check the comments as well, as they provide information on automatically creating the chrooted environment using {{c|emerge --config}}.

